s_on: []\nblocks: [\"TICKET-0250\", \"TICKET-0251\", \"TICKET-0252\", \"TICKET-0253\", \"TICKET-0254\"]\ntags: [orchestrator, instance-paths, config-layering, t4-foundation]\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nCreate `orchestrator/instance_paths.py` — the shared utility module that centralizes all\npath resolution and config loading for the multi-milestone orchestrator. Every other T4\nticket depends on this module existing first.\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `orchestrator/instance_paths.py` created with:\n  - `InstancePaths` dataclass containing all path fields:\n    - `orch_dir`, `instance_dir`\n    - `config_path` (`orch_dir/config.json`)\n    - `config_local_path` (`orch_dir/config.local.json`)\n    - `state_path`, `activity_log`, `pending_gate_path`, `gate_response_path`, `godot_mcp_lock_path`\n    - `results_dir`, `logs_dir`\n    - `prompts_dir`, `schemas_dir` (shared, under `orch_dir`)\n  - `resolve_instance(instance_name: str, orch_dir: Path | None = None) -> InstancePaths`:\n    - `orch_dir` defaults to `$HFS_ORCH_DIR` env var, then `<repo_root>/orchestrator`\n    - `instance_dir = orch_dir / \"instances\" / instance_name`\n    - Creates `instance_dir`, `instance_dir/results`, `instance_dir/logs` on first call\n    - Returns fully populated `InstancePaths`\n  - `load_config(paths: InstancePaths) -> dict`:\n    - Loads `paths.config_path` (required — raises `FileNotFoundError` if absent)\n    - If `paths.config_local_path` exists, deep-merges it on top of defaults\n    - Returns merged dict\n  - `_deep_merge(base: dict, override: dict) -> dict` — private recursive merge helper\n    - Merges leaf values: override wins; sub-dicts are merged recursively, not replaced\n- [ ] Module has no external dependencies beyond stdlib (`pathlib`, `json`, `os`, `dataclasses`)\n- [ ] Module is importable from any script in `orchestrator/`\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Repo root detection: walk up from `__file__` to find the directory containing `orchestrator/`\n- `_deep_merge` must handle nested dicts (not just top-level keys) — e.g., merging\n  `{\"budgets\": {\"session_ceiling_usd\": 10}}` must leave other `budgets` keys intact\n- Do not add a `per_instance_config_path` — the design calls for two layers only (global defaults + global local override)\n\n---\n\n## Handoff Notes\n\n(Leave blank until handoff occurs.)\n\n---\n\n## Activity Log\n\n- 2026-03-01 [producer] Created — T4 Foundation phase\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":2,"oldLines":7,"newStart":2,"newLines":7,"lines":[" id: TICKET-0249"," title: \"Create instance_paths.py shared utility module\""," type: FEATURE","-status: OPEN","+status: IN_PROGRESS"," priority: P1"," owner: systems-programmer"," created_by: producer"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KUNJw1qEEny9teYj8cm5B1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014LE23H7JGrmnvyBghgaCY9","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\tickets\\T4\\TICKET-0249.md","old_string":"- 2026-03-01 [producer] Created — T4 Foundation phase","new_string":"- 2026-03-01 [producer] Created — T4 Foundation phase\n- 2026-03-01 [systems-programmer] Starting work — implementing instance_paths.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":546,"cache_read_input_tokens":37049,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":546},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e112071d-8801-4f85-ac6c-9c5f5e57d0a2","uuid":"4f3cfb48-0dd2-493b-b1ad-29c17d720cbe"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014LE23H7JGrmnvyBghgaCY9","type":"tool_result","content":"The file C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\tickets\\T4\\TICKET-0249.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e112071d-8801-4f85-ac6c-9c5f5e57d0a2","uuid":"bb01785f-4cc8-4508-96d5-ce84f3be147d","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\tickets\\T4\\TICKET-0249.md","oldString":"- 2026-03-01 [producer] Created — T4 Foundation phase","newString":"- 2026-03-01 [producer] Created — T4 Foundation phase\n- 2026-03-01 [systems-programmer] Starting work — implementing instance_paths.py","originalFile":"---\nid: TICKET-0249\ntitle: \"Create instance_paths.py shared utility module\"\ntype: FEATURE\nstatus: IN_PROGRESS\npriority: P1\nowner: systems-programmer\ncreated_by: producer\ncreated_at: 2026-03-01\nupdated_at: 2026-03-01\nmilestone: \"T4\"\nphase: \"Foundation\"\ndepends_on: []\nblocks: [\"TICKET-0250\", \"TICKET-0251\", \"TICKET-0252\", \"TICKET-0253\", \"TICKET-0254\"]\ntags: [orchestrator, instance-paths, config-layering, t4-foundation]\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nCreate `orchestrator/instance_paths.py` — the shared utility module that centralizes all\npath resolution and config loading for the multi-milestone orchestrator. Every other T4\nticket depends on this module existing first.\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `orchestrator/instance_paths.py` created with:\n  - `InstancePaths` dataclass containing all path fields:\n    - `orch_dir`, `instance_dir`\n    - `config_path` (`orch_dir/config.json`)\n    - `config_local_path` (`orch_dir/config.local.json`)\n    - `state_path`, `activity_log`, `pending_gate_path`, `gate_response_path`, `godot_mcp_lock_path`\n    - `results_dir`, `logs_dir`\n    - `prompts_dir`, `schemas_dir` (shared, under `orch_dir`)\n  - `resolve_instance(instance_name: str, orch_dir: Path | None = None) -> InstancePaths`:\n    - `orch_dir` defaults to `$HFS_ORCH_DIR` env var, then `<repo_root>/orchestrator`\n    - `instance_dir = orch_dir / \"instances\" / instance_name`\n    - Creates `instance_dir`, `instance_dir/results`, `instance_dir/logs` on first call\n    - Returns fully populated `InstancePaths`\n  - `load_config(paths: InstancePaths) -> dict`:\n    - Loads `paths.config_path` (required — raises `FileNotFoundError` if absent)\n    - If `paths.config_local_path` exists, deep-merges it on top of defaults\n    - Returns merged dict\n  - `_deep_merge(base: dict, override: dict) -> dict` — private recursive merge helper\n    - Merges leaf values: override wins; sub-dicts are merged recursively, not replaced\n- [ ] Module has no external dependencies beyond stdlib (`pathlib`, `json`, `os`, `dataclasses`)\n- [ ] Module is importable from any script in `orchestrator/`\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Repo root detection: walk up from `__file__` to find the directory containing `orchestrator/`\n- `_deep_merge` must handle nested dicts (not just top-level keys) — e.g., merging\n  `{\"budgets\": {\"session_ceiling_usd\": 10}}` must leave other `budgets` keys intact\n- Do not add a `per_instance_config_path` — the design calls for two layers only (global defaults + global local override)\n\n---\n\n## Handoff Notes\n\n(Leave blank until handoff occurs.)\n\n---\n\n## Activity Log\n\n- 2026-03-01 [producer] Created — T4 Foundation phase\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":67,"oldLines":3,"newStart":67,"newLines":4,"lines":[" ## Activity Log"," "," - 2026-03-01 [producer] Created — T4 Foundation phase","+- 2026-03-01 [systems-programmer] Starting work — implementing instance_paths.py"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011oFt1XcP9shGPMFsiDh3m5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create the `instance_paths.py` module."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":339,"cache_read_input_tokens":37595,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":339},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e112071d-8801-4f85-ac6c-9c5f5e57d0a2","uuid":"fd059dd4-ce29-4243-8bb5-746515342a2d"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011oFt1XcP9shGPMFsiDh3m5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QcsGCTuTqJTiJx4WbbFvPF","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\orchestrator\\instance_paths.py","content":"\"\"\"Shared utility module for multi-milestone orchestrator path resolution and config loading.\n\nCentralizes all path resolution and config loading so every other orchestrator\nmodule uses a single, consistent set of paths per instance.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nimport os\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\n@dataclass(frozen=True)\nclass InstancePaths:\n    \"\"\"All resolved paths for one orchestrator instance.\"\"\"\n\n    # Top-level directories\n    orch_dir: Path\n    instance_dir: Path\n\n    # Global config (shared across instances, lives under orch_dir)\n    config_path: Path\n    config_local_path: Path\n\n    # Per-instance state files\n    state_path: Path\n    activity_log: Path\n    pending_gate_path: Path\n    gate_response_path: Path\n    godot_mcp_lock_path: Path\n\n    # Per-instance output directories\n    results_dir: Path\n    logs_dir: Path\n\n    # Shared directories (under orch_dir)\n    prompts_dir: Path\n    schemas_dir: Path\n\n\ndef resolve_instance(\n    instance_name: str, orch_dir: Path | None = None\n) -> InstancePaths:\n    \"\"\"Resolve all paths for a named orchestrator instance.\n\n    Args:\n        instance_name: The name of the instance (e.g. a milestone identifier).\n        orch_dir: Explicit orchestrator root. Falls back to $HFS_ORCH_DIR,\n                  then to ``<repo_root>/orchestrator``.\n\n    Returns:\n        A fully populated ``InstancePaths`` with directories created as needed.\n    \"\"\"\n    if orch_dir is None:\n        env_dir = os.environ.get(\"HFS_ORCH_DIR\")\n        if env_dir:\n            orch_dir = Path(env_dir)\n        else:\n            # Walk up from this file to find the repo root (parent of orchestrator/)\n            orch_dir = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\n\n    orch_dir = orch_dir.resolve()\n    instance_dir = orch_dir / \"instances\" / instance_name\n\n    # Ensure per-instance directories exist\n    (instance_dir / \"results\").mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    (instance_dir / \"logs\").mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    return InstancePaths(\n        orch_dir=orch_dir,\n        instance_dir=instance_dir,\n        # Global config\n        config_path=orch_dir / \"config.json\",\n        config_local_path=orch_dir / \"config.local.json\",\n        # Per-instance state\n        state_path=instance_dir / \"state.json\",\n        activity_log=instance_dir / \"activity.log\",\n        pending_gate_path=instance_dir / \"pending_gate.json\",\n        gate_response_path=instance_dir / \"gate_response.json\",\n        godot_mcp_lock_path=instance_dir / \"godot_mcp.lock\",\n        # Per-instance output\n        results_dir=instance_dir / \"results\",\n        logs_dir=instance_dir / \"logs\",\n        # Shared\n        prompts_dir=orch_dir / \"prompts\",\n        schemas_dir=orch_dir / \"schemas\",\n    )\n\n\ndef load_config(paths: InstancePaths) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Load and merge orchestrator configuration.\n\n    Reads the required global ``config.json``, then deep-merges\n    ``config.local.json`` on top if it exists.\n\n    Args:\n        paths: Resolved instance paths (only config_path and\n               config_local_path are used).\n\n    Returns:\n        The merged configuration dictionary.\n\n    Raises:\n        FileNotFoundError: If the base ``config.json`` does not exist.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not paths.config_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(\n            f\"Required config file not found: {paths.config_path}\"\n        )\n\n    with open(paths.config_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        config = json.load(f)\n\n    if paths.config_local_path.exists():\n        with open(paths.config_local_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            local_overrides = json.load(f)\n        config = _deep_merge(config, local_overrides)\n\n    return config\n\n\ndef _deep_merge(base: dict, override: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Recursively merge *override* into *base*, returning a new dict.\n\n    - Sub-dicts are merged recursively (not replaced wholesale).\n    - All other values: *override* wins at leaf level.\n\n    Neither input dict is mutated.\n    \"\"\"\n    merged = dict(base)\n    for key, override_value in override.items():\n        base_value = merged.get(key)\n        if isinstance(base_value, dict) and isinstance(override_value, dict):\n            merged[key] = _deep_merge(base_value, override_value)\n        else:\n            merged[key] = override_value\n    return merged\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":339,"cache_read_input_tokens":37595,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":339},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e112071d-8801-4f85-ac6c-9c5f5e57d0a2","uuid":"ed0a7c51-6f90-4830-b59b-d70c28838924"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QcsGCTuTqJTiJx4WbbFvPF","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\orchestrator\\instance_paths.py"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e112071d-8801-4f85-ac6c-9c5f5e57d0a2","uuid":"94f81f85-1e93-4c53-8f97-515c975c07fb","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\orchestrator\\instance_paths.py","content":"\"\"\"Shared utility module for multi-milestone orchestrator path resolution and config loading.\n\nCentralizes all path resolution and config loading so every other orchestrator\nmodule uses a single, consistent set of paths per instance.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nimport os\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\n@dataclass(frozen=True)\nclass InstancePaths:\n    \"\"\"All resolved paths for one orchestrator instance.\"\"\"\n\n    # Top-level directories\n    orch_dir: Path\n    instance_dir: Path\n\n    # Global config (shared across instances, lives under orch_dir)\n    config_path: Path\n    config_local_path: Path\n\n    # Per-instance state files\n    state_path: Path\n    activity_log: Path\n    pending_gate_path: Path\n    gate_response_path: Path\n    godot_mcp_lock_path: Path\n\n    # Per-instance output directories\n    results_dir: Path\n    logs_dir: Path\n\n    # Shared directories (under orch_dir)\n    prompts_dir: Path\n    schemas_dir: Path\n\n\ndef resolve_instance(\n    instance_name: str, orch_dir: Path | None = None\n) -> InstancePaths:\n    \"\"\"Resolve all paths for a named orchestrator instance.\n\n    Args:\n        instance_name: The name of the instance (e.g. a milestone identifier).\n        orch_dir: Explicit orchestrator root. Falls back to $HFS_ORCH_DIR,\n                  then to ``<repo_root>/orchestrator``.\n\n    Returns:\n        A fully populated ``InstancePaths`` with directories created as needed.\n    \"\"\"\n    if orch_dir is None:\n        env_dir = os.environ.get(\"HFS_ORCH_DIR\")\n        if env_dir:\n            orch_dir = Path(env_dir)\n        else:\n            # Walk up from this file to find the repo root (parent of orchestrator/)\n            orch_dir = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\n\n    orch_dir = orch_dir.resolve()\n    instance_dir = orch_dir / \"instances\" / instance_name\n\n    # Ensure per-instance directories exist\n    (instance_dir / \"results\").mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    (instance_dir / \"logs\").mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    return InstancePaths(\n        orch_dir=orch_dir,\n        instance_dir=instance_dir,\n        # Global config\n        config_path=orch_dir / \"config.json\",\n        config_local_path=orch_dir / \"config.local.json\",\n        # Per-instance state\n        state_path=instance_dir / \"state.json\",\n        activity_log=instance_dir / \"activity.log\",\n        pending_gate_path=instance_dir / \"pending_gate.json\",\n        gate_response_path=instance_dir / \"gate_response.json\",\n        godot_mcp_lock_path=instance_dir / \"godot_mcp.lock\",\n        # Per-instance output\n        results_dir=instance_dir / \"results\",\n        logs_dir=instance_dir / \"logs\",\n        # Shared\n        prompts_dir=orch_dir / \"prompts\",\n        schemas_dir=orch_dir / \"schemas\",\n    )\n\n\ndef load_config(paths: InstancePaths) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Load and merge orchestrator configuration.\n\n    Reads the required global ``config.json``, then deep-merges\n    ``config.local.json`` on top if it exists.\n\n    Args:\n        paths: Resolved instance paths (only config_path and\n               config_local_path are used).\n\n    Returns:\n        The merged configuration dictionary.\n\n    Raises:\n        FileNotFoundError: If the base ``config.json`` does not exist.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not paths.config_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(\n            f\"Required config file not found: {paths.config_path}\"\n        )\n\n    with open(paths.config_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        config = json.load(f)\n\n    if paths.config_local_path.exists():\n        with open(paths.config_local_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            local_overrides = json.load(f)\n        config = _deep_merge(config, local_overrides)\n\n    return config\n\n\ndef _deep_merge(base: dict, override: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Recursively merge *override* into *base*, returning a new dict.\n\n    - Sub-dicts are merged recursively (not replaced wholesale).\n    - All other values: *override* wins at leaf level.\n\n    Neither input dict is mutated.\n    \"\"\"\n    merged = dict(base)\n    for key, override_value in override.items():\n        base_value = merged.get(key)\n        if isinstance(base_value, dict) and isinstance(override_value, dict):\n            merged[key] = _deep_merge(base_value, override_value)\n        else:\n            merged[key] = override_value\n    return merged\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QTLBUgx37bHn7cc74KBDRo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me verify the module is importable and test it."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1393,"cache_read_input_tokens":37934,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1393},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e112071d-8801-4f85-ac6c-9c5f5e57d0a2","uuid":"864ffe4f-f4e0-4b2a-a4f3-38974fa9936d"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QTLBUgx37bHn7cc74KBDRo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KPyYLDg1spgD7YPaGUbd2c","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd C:/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio && python -c \"\nfrom orchestrator.instance_paths import resolve_instance, load_config, _deep_merge, InstancePaths\nimport tempfile, json, os\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Test 1: _deep_merge basic\nresult = _deep_merge({'a': 1, 'b': {'x': 10, 'y': 20}}, {'b': {'y': 99, 'z': 30}, 'c': 3})\nassert result == {'a': 1, 'b': {'x': 10, 'y': 99, 'z': 30}, 'c': 3}, f'deep_merge failed: {result}'\nprint('PASS: _deep_merge basic')\n\n# Test 2: _deep_merge nested\nresult = _deep_merge(\n    {'budgets': {'session_ceiling_usd': 10, 'default_worker_usd': 3}},\n    {'budgets': {'session_ceiling_usd': 50}}\n)\nassert result == {'budgets': {'session_ceiling_usd': 50, 'default_worker_usd': 3}}, f'nested merge failed: {result}'\nprint('PASS: _deep_merge nested')\n\n# Test 3: _deep_merge does not mutate inputs\nbase = {'a': {'x': 1}}\noverride = {'a': {'y': 2}}\nresult = _deep_merge(base, override)\nassert base == {'a': {'x': 1}}, 'base was mutated'\nassert override == {'a': {'y': 2}}, 'override was mutated'\nprint('PASS: _deep_merge immutability')\n\n# Test 4: resolve_instance with explicit orch_dir\nwith tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmp:\n    orch = Path(tmp)\n    paths = resolve_instance('test-instance', orch_dir=orch)\n    assert paths.orch_dir == orch.resolve()\n    assert paths.instance_dir == orch.resolve() / 'instances' / 'test-instance'\n    assert paths.config_path == orch.resolve() / 'config.json'\n    assert paths.config_local_path == orch.resolve() / 'config.local.json'\n    assert paths.state_path == paths.instance_dir / 'state.json'\n    assert paths.results_dir.exists()\n    assert paths.logs_dir.exists()\n    assert paths.prompts_dir == orch.resolve() / 'prompts'\n    assert paths.schemas_dir == orch.resolve() / 'schemas'\n    print('PASS: resolve_instance basic')\n\n# Test 5: resolve_instance with env var\nwith tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmp:\n    os.environ['HFS_ORCH_DIR'] = tmp\n    paths = resolve_instance('env-test')\n    assert paths.orch_dir == Path(tmp).resolve()\n    del os.environ['HFS_ORCH_DIR']\n    print('PASS: resolve_instance env var')\n\n# Test 6: resolve_instance defaults to __file__ parent\npaths = resolve_instance('default-test')\nexpected_orch = Path('orchestrator').resolve()\n# Should be the orchestrator directory\nassert 'orchestrator' in str(paths.orch_dir)\nprint('PASS: resolve_instance default')\n\n# Test 7: load_config raises FileNotFoundError\nwith tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmp:\n    paths = resolve_instance('missing-config', orch_dir=Path(tmp))\n    try:\n        load_config(paths)\n        assert False, 'Should have raised FileNotFoundError'\n    except FileNotFoundError:\n        print('PASS: load_config FileNotFoundError')\n\n# Test 8: load_config with base only\nwith tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmp:\n    orch = Path(tmp)\n    config = {'models': {'default': 'sonnet'}, 'budgets': {'max': 10}}\n    (orch / 'config.json').write_text(json.dumps(config))\n    paths = resolve_instance('config-test', orch_dir=orch)\n    loaded = load_config(paths)\n    assert loaded == config\n    print('PASS: load_config base only')\n\n# Test 9: load_config with local override\nwith tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmp:\n    orch = Path(tmp)\n    base = {'models': {'default': 'sonnet', 'producer': 'haiku'}, 'budgets': {'max': 10}}\n    local = {'models': {'default': 'opus'}, 'extra': True}\n    (orch / 'config.json').write_text(json.dumps(base))\n    (orch / 'config.local.json').write_text(json.dumps(local))\n    paths = resolve_instance('merge-test', orch_dir=orch)\n    loaded = load_config(paths)\n    assert loaded == {'models': {'default': 'opus', 'producer': 'haiku'}, 'budgets': {'max': 10}, 'extra': True}\n    print('PASS: load_config with local merge')\n\nprint()\nprint('All tests passed!')\n\"\n","description":"Run comprehensive tests for instance_paths.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1393,"cache_read_input_tokens":37934,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1393},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e112071d-8801-4f85-ac6c-9c5f5e57d0a2","uuid":"1548eef9-bb48-4fba-997e-46834fb2138a"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KPyYLDg1spgD7YPaGUbd2c","type":"tool_result","content":"PASS: _deep_merge basic\r\nPASS: _deep_merge nested\r\nPASS: _deep